'''Troll-friendly''' is a term used to describe an internet community that does not take any steps to combat [[Internet_troll|trolling]]. Such policies, in particular, restrict administrators and sysops from applying policies to control trolling. In contrast, some communities actively discourage trolling, these communities are known as '''not troll-friendly'''. In a troll-friendly community, trolls believe that if someone participates in the sysop power structure, they should be driven off.<ref>Consumerium Development Wiki Contributors: "Troll-friendly", Consumerium Development Wiki, 2004</ref>

